Record Class FunctionParameterResolver

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.function.resolver.FunctionParameterResolver
Record Components:
evaluationContext - The evaluation context for resolving variables and executing expressions
input - The input collection that the function will operate on
actualArguments - The list of FHIRPath expressions that will be bound to function parameters
public record FunctionParameterResolver(EvaluationContext evaluationContext, Collection input, List<FhirPath> actualArguments) extends Record
Resolves function parameters for method-defined FHIRPath functions.

    • bind

      @Nonnull public FunctionInvocation bind(@Nonnull Method method)
      Binds the input and arguments to the specified method.

      This method performs type checking and conversion of FHIRPath expressions to Java objects that can be passed to the method. It validates that:

      • The method has at least one parameter (for the input)
      • The number of arguments does not exceed the method's parameter count
      • Required parameters have corresponding arguments
      • Arguments can be converted to the expected parameter types
      Parameters:
      method - The method to bind parameters to
      Returns:
      A FunctionInvocation object ready to be executed
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - if the method has no parameters
      InvalidUserInputError - if the arguments cannot be bound to the parameters
